The paper deals with multimodal sentiment analysis, which involves processing and relating information from language, visual, and acoustic modalities. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, given that the paper proposes a method based on sequence to sequence models, which are commonly used in natural language processing, and that the paper achieves state-of-the-art results on multimodal sentiment analysis datasets, which are often used in natural language processing and multimedia research, it is most likely that the paper belongs to the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The other categories are still possible, but less likely.
